This is how to rolling_max of numbers:
   Remember that result is []
   Remember that n is numbers's length
   When n is 0, then:
      The answer is result
   End when
   Remember that current_max is item 0 in numbers
   Add result to current_max
   Remember that i is 1
   Do this diff of n and 1 times:
      Remember that x is item i in numbers
      When x is more than current_max, then:
         Remember that current_max is x
      End when
      Add result to current_max
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is result
